The Air Task Force of Operation Lafiya Dole has executed air strikes which neutralized several Islamic State of West Africa Province fighters at Kolloram which is on the fringes of the Lake Chad in Borno State. Coordinator, Defence Media Operation, Major-General John Enenche, in a statement yesterday, said the troops got credible intelligence reports indicating that some of the ISWAP leaders and fighters had converged on the settlement for a meeting. He noted that the NAF fighter jets and surveillance aircraft were scrambled to attack the location. He said that the few survivors were taken out in subsequent passes as the jets strafed the area. Nigerian troop neutralises several ISWAP fighters in Borno Air Force jets destroy terrorist structures, neutralize fighters in Borno NAF jets destroy terrorist structures, neutralize fighters at Bakassi in Borno